title: Mission impossible: Abandoned Soviet space rocket waits for lift-off derelict hanger, in pictures
text:
Previous slide Next slide 1 of 10 View All Skip Ad 
A photographer has managed to gain access to a disused hanger to photograph a Soviet rocket dating back to the 1970s. Ralph Mirebs visited an area of the Baikonur Cosmodrome in Kazakhstan to take these atmospheric images of a relic of the Russian/US space race. Ralph Mirebs/Exclusivepix Media
